Availability API for ECv1"}], "subcloud": "FY27 SC M4 AFCC - Digital", "target_release": "264", "theme": "\u26ab Not Prioritized"}, {"health": "Watch", "health_comments": "27-May: Messaging Core team on track at 64% with bug fixes in progress. Whatsapp India team at Watch (47% complete) with Q2/Q3 testing in-progress. Target ETA: 6/29 for Meta GA after which Meta will begin external rollout.\r\nOn-track for flow usecases. Messaging Core team is code complete on WA Flow with Endpoints (33%) and waiting for MCF deliverables to start integration testing. Dynamic Flows carry-over remains on track at 11%. WA India team\u0027s Flow Endpoints epic (80% complete) has spike document out for review. Flow Submission After Session will be picked up in June per WA India team.\r\n20-May: Q2 and Q3 testing is actively underway with the team monitoring for open bugs. Cautious Watch, 3 teams are testing, so-far no blockers submitted. Targeting 6/29 for Meta GA after which Meta will roll out in Jul for few countries and then in Aug for the rest. WA India team continues progress across template features: Media Card Carousels (Watch, 64% complete; inner-sourcing spike completed, final call next week on Feature Freeze commitment), WhatsApp Payment India: On-Track.\r\n13-May: CSI team support provided, innersourcing done as well. Testing ongoing as per the plan. On-track.\r\n6-May: On-track, cautious call-out on the CSI team dependency and planning to overcome that with inner-sourcing. Not a blocker or need LT support.", "id": "a1fEE0000003447YAA", "name": "[264] Best in Class Whatsapp Experiences", "portfolio": "FY27 SC M4 AFCC - Digital", "program_manager": "Sivaprakasam Ganesan", "projects": [{"epics": [{"end_date": "2026-06-03", "health": "Watch", "health_comments": "May 13, 2026: Q2 and Q3 testing is actively underway with the team monitoring for open bugs. As noted in the last AFCC call, we remain in a cautious Watch stage at this point. 3 teams are testing, so far no blockers subm