J - For Global Expansion (BYOC/WA/Resell)", "number": "7"}, {"end_date": "2026-06-03", "health": "On Track", "health_comments": "-", "health_status": "On Track", "name": "[264] CUJ - End-to-End Voice Stream Including Human Agent Leg", "number": "9"}, {"end_date": "2026-05-21", "health": "Not Started", "health_comments": "-", "health_status": "Not Started", "name": "[264] CUJ - DR Detection and Alerting via Kaiju/CUJ Framework", "number": "10"}], "name": "[264] Critical User Journeys"}], "subcloud": "FY27 SC M4 AFCC - Voice", "target_release": "264", "theme": "\u26ab Not Prioritized"}, {"health": "On Track", "health_comments": "6/3: On-track. Team prepping for the 262 Tech Deep Dive and partnering with the CCAI team on QM for Cases. Key progress includes updated prompt templates for automated multi-rep interaction evaluation, and audio redaction advances spanning conversation handling, permissions, redaction model development, auto-purge, and recording export.\r\n\r\n5/26: On-track. 1) QM: Setup config, post-call form mapping, and runtime evaluation progressing. LLM prompt construction and token management, telemetry, and form testing for automated QM in flight. \r\n2) Call Recording: Audio redaction design closed; conversation message handling and startup initialization advancing. Redaction model, auto-purge capability, recording timestamp accuracy, and the exporter setup in progress.\r\n\r\n5/20: On-track. Both projects progressing well. 1) QM - completed AQM setup. Form mapping and prompt templates in progress. 2) Call Recording - completed the audio redaction design doc and model creation for redaction in progress.\r\n\r\n5/12: On-track. 1) QM - Incorporating Data Model changes and LLM model testing in progress. 2) Call Recording - Sensitive Data Rules (SDR) changes review scheduled with Conversation team.\r\n\r\n5/5 - On Track\r\nQM - Data model changes for AQM finalized. LLM model testing in progress.\r\nCall Recording - Design of PII redaction from audio recor